 ### Failure modes
 
+The per-tick rule sequence is fixed: pre-seal guard → re-read +
+validate `reckoner.schedulerConfig` → query held petitions →
+source/disabled gates → dependency gate → dedupe (scheduler-path
+only) → `evaluate` → apply decisions.
+
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no acceptance/decline row, no transition. The dedupe runs inside the scheduler call and counts only non-deferred prior rows — the dependency gate (which runs *before* the scheduler) re-evaluates every tick regardless. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started` resolved the active scheduler    | Fail-loud throw at handler entry (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved — phase:started has not fired`). Production never trips this; tests get a deterministic loud signal. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] tick:` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows for any writ). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no rows for any writ). |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue (other in-scope decisions still apply). |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped — no decision is applied for any writ. |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; that one decision is ignored. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | The writ is filtered out before `SchedulerInput` is built; no `evaluate` call for it, no acceptance/decline row, no transition. The dedupe filter only counts non-deferred prior rows — the dependency gate (which runs *before* dedupe) re-evaluates every tick regardless. |
+| Empty candidate set                                                | Early return after the held-petition query; no `evaluate` call, no rows, no errors. |
 
